10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Ahrefs is best suited for link builders, SEO agencies, content marketers, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Yoast SEO, meanwhile, shines for WordPress beginners, bloggers, small websites, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2010, Ahrefs describes itself as \"Comprehensive SEO toolset known for the best backlink index in the industry.\" Yoast SEO, established in 2010, positions itself as \"The most popular WordPress SEO plugin for on-page optimization.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Ahrefs** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 7.0), more features (10 vs 2). However, this does not mean Yoast SEO is a poor choice — far from it. Yoast SEO excels in its own right, particularly for WordPress beginners and bloggers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best backlink database in the industry, go with Ahrefs. If industry standard wordpress seo plugin matters more to you, Yoast SEO is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
